{"id":"281607493_Eigenvalue_confinement_and_spectral_gap_for_random_simplicial_complexes","abstract":"We consider the adjacency operator of the Linial-Meshulam model for random\nsimplicial complexes on $n$ vertices, where each $d$-cell is added\nindependently with probability $p$ to the complete $(d-1)$-skeleton. Under the\nassumption $np(1-p) \\gg \\log^4 n$, we prove that the spectral gap between the\n$\\binom{n-1}{d}$ smallest eigenvalues and the remaining $\\binom{n-1}{d-1}$\neigenvalues is $np - 2\\sqrt{dnp(1-p)} \\, (1 + o(1))$ with high probability.\nThis estimate follows from a more general result on eigenvalue confinement. In\naddition, we prove that the global distribution of the eigenvalues is\nasymptotically given by the semicircle law. The main ingredient of the proof is\na F\\\"uredi-Koml\\'os-type argument for random simplicial complexes, which may be\nregarded as sparse random matrix models with dependent entries.","authors":["Antti Knowles","Ron Rosenthal"],"meta":["September 2015Random Structures and Algorithms 51(3)","DOI:10.1002/rsa.20710","SourcearXiv"],"references":["303657440_Local_law_and_Tracy-Widom_limit_for_sparse_random_matrices","278413824_On_Expansion_and_Topological_Overlap","266561070_On_the_phase_transition_in_random_simplicial_complexes","265386034_Isoperimetric_Inequalities_for_Ramanujan_Complexes_and_Topological_Expanders","264424907_Local_spectral_expansion_approach_to_high_dimensional_expanders","264385377_Mixing_Properties_and_the_Chromatic_Number_of_Ramanujan_Complexes","263426973_Spectrum_and_combinatorics_of_two-dimensional_Ramanujan_complexes","259657641_Higher_Dimensional_Discrete_Cheeger_Inequalities","258082373_Random_Walks_on_Simplicial_Complexes_and_Harmonics","256186709_The_Threshold_for_Integer_Homology_in_Random_d-Complexes","249316066_Random_Latin_squares_and_2-dimensional_expanders","239939678_On_the_chromatic_number_of_a_simplicial_complex","234060060_Ramanujan_Complexes_and_High_Dimensional_Expanders","228102827